article.headline: Vermont 55, Cent. Connecticut St. 48
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Mike Trimboli had 12 points to lead Vermont while Chris Holm and Joe Trapani each had 11 as Vermont beat Central Connecticut 55-48 Thursday night. Vermont (8-5) struggled offensively but held Central Connecticut (3-9) to 28.3 percent shooting. Vermont shot 40.4 percent, but closed the game with a 21-13 run over the last 13:47. Central was led by 18 points and 11 boards from Obie Nwadike. An 8-0 run to start the second half gave Central Connecticut a 31-30 lead. The charge was capped by a 3-pointer from the right wing by Javier Mojica to put Central Connecticut up for the first time since holding a 3-2 advantage in the opening moments of the game. Vermont used an 8-0 run of their own to take a 42-35 lead with 11:22 to go. Central Connecticut pulled to within five once more, but its offense sputtered down the stretch, allowing Vermont to pull away.
